def merge_sorted_lists(list1_f, list2_f):
    merged_list = []
    i, j = 0, 0
    while i < len(list1_f) and j < len(list2_f):
        if list1_f[i] < list2_f[j]:
            merged_list.append(list1_f[i])
            i += 1
        else:
            merged_list.append(list2_f[j])
            j += 1
    merged_list.extend(list1_f[i:])
    merged_list.extend(list2_f[j:])
    return merged_list
